  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Send transaction screen: if tap inside Amount field then keyboard is opened but field is hidden, so user can't see what's being typed. I would expect that focus is in the Amount field and that field is fully visible to me, so I do not need to scroll to it. It happens on several Android phones, e.g. Samsung galaxy S6, S7 and  ZTE A2017G (screenHeight 2560, screenWidth 1440)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nfocus is in the Amount field and that field is fully visible to me, so I do not need to scroll to it. \r\n![screenshot_20180214-163710](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/36207151-f13766f2-11a5-11e8-8bbf-378401e215e5.png)\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nAmount field is hidden behind keyboard. To see what's being typed I need to scroll the screen\r\n![screenshot_20180214-163703](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/36207145-ed947f1c-11a5-11e8-9728-4dececd968d3.png)\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nFrom 00:18 https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/7699096/sessions/28/?accessToken=qUKITizgAWjQdFbXqsuMyIjaXpU\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open Wallet\r\n- Tap on Send transaction\r\n- Tap on Amount field and start typing the amount\r\n- Check that you can see the field and what's typed\r\nSame issue happens if select recipient and after this tap in Amount field.\r\nNote: if scroll to the amount field once then second time you tap on the field screen scrolls as expected.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.13 and nightly build Feb 14\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n",
